b"Frida is on a mission to make sure her friends can breathe fresh, clean air while on the farm. AGCO's filtration systems force air out of a space, preventing unfiltered outdoor air from entering the animal living areas. This ensures top air quality and helps them live a healthy life.\r\n\r\n#FridaTheAmbassador #AGCO #farmlife #farmdog #farmanimals #barn #barnlife"

b"Some of Frida's best pals on the farm are horses, but the hens are right on their hooves. Hens need a safe place to lay eggs and our mechanical nesting systems help provide that and in the process reduce stress and enhance hatchability. Do you have livestock on your farm? Let us know in the comments!\n#FridaTheAmbassador #hens #farmlife #farmer #agriculture #livestock"

Now available for Valtra G, N, and T Series machines.

b':police_car_light: Introducing the #MasseyFerguson 1800E and 2800E Series compact tractors :police_car_light:

Featuring 4-wheel drive, powered by Iseki diesel engines and high-capacity hydraulics, this series is currently available in the US and in five models ranging from 24 to 57.3 engine horsepower.

Contact your local dealer for more information.

#AGCO #tractor #compacttractor #farming #farmlife'

b"Providing detailed 3D images that help farmers monitor for moisture within stored grain, AGCO's newly acquired GrainViz is a high-tech solution that gives our customers unparalleled insight into their operations. Compared to traditional systems, GrainViz: 

:red_triangle_pointed_up: Uses sensors instead of cables
:red_triangle_pointed_up: Views 100% of moisture content
:red_triangle_pointed_up: Identifies problem spots before they become issues
:red_triangle_pointed_up: Is cloud-based with the latest technology updates

#AGCO #GrainViz #grainstorage #GSI #agriculture #farming #farmlife #3D #agtech"

b'The next generation of field robots from AGCO has more than just a new appearance - its inner workings are also brand new. Among its many innovative features, the Fendt Xaver's sensors are able to measure soil moisture, temperature, humus content, and plant residues. This allows the robot to plant grains at depths and strengths specific to local conditions. 

Another plus? "Fendt Xaver is also integrated into the FendtONE platform and can be managed together with the rest of the machine fleet."

#AGCO #Fendt #FendtOne #FendtXaver #Xaver #smartfarming #agriculture #farming #innovation #robot #robots'

b'Every planting season is different, and there are many factors that contribute to success, including:

:red_triangle_pointed_up: No-till and crop rotation
:red_triangle_pointed_up: Planting date
:red_triangle_pointed_up: Seed quality
:red_triangle_pointed_up: Crop nutrition

Share your #PlantingSeason tips in the comments below! 

#AGCO #MasseyFerguson #Fuse #SmartFarming #planting #agriculture #farming'

b"Yesterday marked the launch of AGCO South Africa's new two-tier distribution model making it easier for dealers and farmers to connect. Dealers will now have more control and the ability to offer more efficient services to farmers.

Improving customer service for farmers and the profitability of AGCO\xe2\x80\x99s dealers remains a top priority.

#AGCO #supplymanagement #AGCOAfrica #MasseyFerguson #Fendt #Challenger #Valtra"

b'Join the #AGCOAgricultureFoundation ShareTheMeal team and donate by tapping the link in our bio.
.
COVID-19 is deepening food and nutrition insecurity for children and farmers. AAF donated $100,000 to @WFPUSA this year in support of relief efforts, and now seeks to double the impact.
.
That\xe2\x80\x99s why today, the AGCO Agriculture Foundation (AAF) is launching a new campaign to feed 342 more children for a year. Tap the link in our bio to join in.
.
#agriculture #covid19 #zerohunger #endhunger #instagood #food #farmers #nutrition #children #ahandup'

b"With at least 500M of the world's estimated 570M farms being managed by families, family farming remains dominant in global agriculture. Ryan Davidson of Davidson Farm shared his road to success over the course of five generations: \xe2\x80\x9cThis farm has been in the family for almost 120 years. They lived through the \xe2\x80\x9930s, the \xe2\x80\x9980s\xe2\x80\xa6 they made it work. Am I doing good by them? It\xe2\x80\x99s what I strive for every day.\xe2\x80\x9d In the end, legacy is what inspires him to move forward.

Is your farm family managed? Let us know in the comments!

#NationalFamilyDay #FamilyDay #FamilyFarm #FarmLife #AGCO #DavidsonFarm"

b"In the spirit of collaboration and giving, AGCO's TRAIT ambassadors in South Africa came together to collect resources a rural farming community was in need of. 

When delivering the donations to Divine House, a local organization committed to helping members of the community, the TRAIT ambassadors saw an opportunity to share agronomy and technical knowledge on AGCO machines and implements to the emerging farmers around the community.

We are excited to see this budding relationship continue to grow.

#WeAreAGCO #AGCO #giveback"

b'Our focus on risk management for more than 15 years has helped us navigate one of our toughest challenges yet - COVID-19. 

The digital tools we have woven throughout the supply chain were integral to minimizing risk and disruption. Technologies like risk notifications, visualization tools, and an e-sourcing platform allowed us to quickly develop alternate sources of supply and transportation modes. Supplying critical #PPE that allowed suppliers in affected areas to remain in production enabled us to continue providing the best service possible in a safe manner.

#AGCO #COVID19 #supplychain'

b'Using data collected from the field is key to optimizing crop yield. Precision Planting product manager, Ryan Allgaier, shares 4 checkpoints for making agronomic decisions:

:keycap_1: In-cab display alerts with in-the-moment tweaks to improve performance
:keycap_2: Second field pass alterations using data from the first pass
:keycap_3: Insights from metrics applied in-season
:keycap_4: Assessing equipment or practice changes needed for the next crop cycle

#AGCO #agronomy #SmartFarming #PrecisionPlanting'

b"Over the last 30 years we've brought together decades of collective know-how to become a market leader with the broadest product line in the agricultural equipment industry. \xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
Since our start in 1990, AGCO has integrated approximately forty companies into one global organization. Each brand in the AGCO family has contributed to our goal of providing the tools farmers need to sustainably grow more while using less. Our approach of smart thinking, smart solutions and smart impact is helping move our business and industry forward. \xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
We are proud of what we've achieved so far and excited at the possibility of where we're able to go. #WeAreAGCO \xe2\x81\xa3
